Bob's Discount Furniture is an American regional chain of privately owned furniture stores in the Northeast, Mid-Atlantic & Midwestern United States.[11] Bob's Discount Furniture started in Connecticut and its corporate headquarters are in Manchester, CT. The company has stores located in Maine, New Hampshire, Massachusetts, Connecticut, Rhode Island, New York, New Jersey, Maryland, Virginia, Pennsylvania, Delaware, and Illinois. In fall 2016, three new stores opened – Wharton, NJ, Hagerstown, MD & Riverdale, NY. – bringing the total number of Bob’s Discount Furniture stores to 76.[12] Bob's Discount Furniture is continuing to expand in 2017, with new stores coming to the Chicago & St. Louis markets.[13]
The company was founded in 1991 with its first store in Newington, Connecticut.[1] Bob's Discount Furniture is based in Manchester, Connecticut and is ranked 14th among U.S. furniture stores.[14] In addition to being known for its distinctive advertisements, the company is also known for offering amenities at many of its stores, which may include an in-store cafe with complimentary refreshments. Many of the stores have a back room where people can get items that are considered imperfect; this area is called The "Outlet". Bob's is also a main sponsor for several professional sports teams; including the Washington Redskins, New England Patriots, Pittsburgh Steelers, and New York Giants. In recent years, NFL players like Chandler Jones (Patriots) and Rashad Jennings (Giants) have had living room sets named after them.[3][15][16][17]



