Executive Profile
Edmond J. English  Executive Chairman, Bob's Discount Furniture LLCAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 4 Board Members in 4 different organizations across 8 different industries.See Board Relationships64--
Background

		Mr. Edmond J. English, also known as Ted, has been the Executive Chairman of Bob's Discount Furniture, Inc., since March 2016 and served as its Chief Executive Officer from November 2006 to March 2016. Mr. English joined The TJX Companies, Inc. in 1983 and served as its Chief Executive Officer from 2000 to September 13, 2005 and President from 1999 to September 13, 2005. He served as Chief Operating Officer of TJX from 1999 to 2000, Senior Vice President and Group Executive ... from 1998 to 1999, Executive Vice President of Merchandising, Planning and Allocation of The Marmaxx Group from 1997 to 1998. He served as Senior Vice President of Merchandising at TJX from 1995 to 1997 and held various merchandising positions with it from 1983 to 1995. Mr. English has more than 30 years in the retail business. Mr. English serves as a Board Chairman of Boston Medical Center Corp. He served as the Chairman of The Marmaxx Group from 2000 to 2004. He serves as a Member of Board of Trustees at Citizens Bank of Massachusetts. He has been a Director of Burlington Coat Factory Investments Holdings, Inc. since November 2016. He has been an Independent Director of Burlington Stores, Inc. since November 15, 2016. He serves as a Director of Rue La La. He served as a Director of Citizens Financial Group, Inc. and Citizens Bank, N.A. He served as a Director of The TJX Companies, Inc. from 1999 to September 13, 2005 and BJ's Wholesale Club Inc. from September 27, 2006 to September 30, 2011. He serves as a Board of Trustees of various funds within the multi-affiliate structure of Natixis Global Asset Management, a global asset management firm. Mr. English is a Member of the Honorary Board of Directors for the Special Olympics of Massachusetts and a Member of the Board of the New England Chapter of Autism Speaks. He is a Member of Board of Trustees at Northeastern University. He was recognized by numerous civic and not-for-profit organizations for his work in the corporate arena and community.Read Full Background




